{
  "doc_id": "43001",
  "text": "For multiple alignments, sequences were retrieved from the NCBI or UniProtKB/SWISS-PROT databases, aligned with clustalW and edited with GeneDoc. Bioedit program was also used for visual inspection and graphical generation of sequence alignments. The molecular graphics softwares, PyMol [CITATION_1] and Coot [CITATION_2] were used for visualization and interaction analysis. Schematic 2D interacting plots were generated using the program LigPlot [CITATION_3] . The Figure 6a was produced using successively MolScript [CITATION_4] and Raster3D [CITATION_5] programs. ",
